BBC America has renewed its acclaimed “Killing Eve” for a fourth season, months ahead of its Season 3 premiere this spring.
“How could we not have massive confidence in ‘Killing Eve’?
Season 3 lead writer Suzanne Heathcote takes Eve, Villanelle and Carolyn to places more thrilling, twisted and surprising than ever.
Our addicted fans will not be disappointed.”“I am beyond thrilled that we can continue our extraordinary journey,” said executive producer Sally Woodward Gentle.
Season 2 of “Killing Eve” had the highest rate of growth of any returning TV drama since the final season of AMC’s “Breaking Bad” in 2013, doubling its freshman audience in Live+SD ratings.